{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":560,"text":"Charles Van Doren, who was later\na senior editor of Britannica,"},{"time":3719,"text":"said the ideal encyclopedia\nshould be radical --"},{"time":6920,"text":"it should stop being safe."},{"time":8480,"text":"But if you know anything about the history\nof Britannica since 1962,"},{"time":11720,"text":"it was anything but radical:"},{"time":13080,"text":"still a very completely safe,\nstodgy type of encyclopedia."},{"time":18000,"text":"Wikipedia, on the other hand,\nbegins with a very radical idea,"},{"time":22200,"text":"and that's for all of us\nto imagine a world"},{"time":24240,"text":"in which every single person on the planet"},{"time":26280,"text":"is given free access\nto the sum of all human knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28880,"text":"And that's what we're doing."},{"time":31000,"text":"So Wikipedia --"},{"time":32183,"text":"you just saw the little\ndemonstration of it --"},{"time":34640,"text":"it's a freely licensed encyclopedia."},{"time":36760,"text":"It's written by thousands of volunteers"},{"time":38642,"text":"all over the world\nin many, many languages."},{"time":41320,"text":"It's written using wiki software --"},{"time":43080,"text":"which is the type of software\nhe just demonstrated --"},{"time":45660,"text":"so anyone can quickly edit and save,"},{"time":47399,"text":"and it goes live\non the Internet immediately."},{"time":50640,"text":"And everything about Wikipedia is managed\nby virtually an all-volunteer staff."},{"time":55280,"text":"So when Yochai is talking\nabout new methods of organization,"},{"time":59720,"text":"he's exactly describing Wikipedia."},{"time":62240,"text":"And what I'm going to do today"},{"time":63693,"text":"is tell you a little bit more\nabout how it really works on the inside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67960,"text":"So Wikipedia's owned\nby the Wikimedia Foundation,"},{"time":71120,"text":"which I founded,"},{"time":72360,"text":"a nonprofit organization."},{"time":73800,"text":"And our goal, the core aim\nof the Wikimedia Foundation,"},{"time":77840,"text":"is to get a free encyclopedia\nto every single person on the planet."},{"time":81040,"text":"And so, if you think\nabout what that means,"},{"time":83080,"text":"it means a lot more\nthan just building a cool website."},{"time":85640,"text":"We're really interested\nin all the issues of the digital divide,"},{"time":88680,"text":"poverty worldwide,"},{"time":90280,"text":"empowering people everywhere\nto have the information that they need"},{"time":93680,"text":"to make good decisions."},{"time":94920,"text":"And so we're going\nto have to do a lot of work"},{"time":97520,"text":"that goes beyond just the Internet."},{"time":99240,"text":"And so that's a big part of why\nwe've chosen the free licensing model,"},{"time":102560,"text":"because that empowers local\nentrepreneurs or anyone who wants to --"},{"time":105823,"text":"they can take our content\nand do anything they like with it --"},{"time":108759,"text":"you can copy it, redistribute it --"},{"time":110465,"text":"and you can do it\ncommercially or non-commercially."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112901,"text":"So there's a lot of opportunities\nthat are going to arise around Wikipedia"},{"time":116425,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":118480,"text":"We're funded by donations from the public,"},{"time":120520,"text":"and one of the more\ninteresting things about that"},{"time":123000,"text":"is how little money\nit actually takes to run Wikipedia."},{"time":126840,"text":"So Yochai showed you the graph\nof what the cost of a printing press was."},{"time":131400,"text":"And I'm going to tell you\nwhat the cost of Wikipedia is."},{"time":134760,"text":"But first, I'll show you how big it is."},{"time":136642,"text":"So we've got over 600,000\narticles in English."},{"time":141040,"text":"We've got two million total articles\nacross many, many different languages."},{"time":145520,"text":"The biggest languages\nare German, Japanese, French --"},{"time":148800,"text":"all the Western-European\nlanguages are quite big."},{"time":152520,"text":"But only around one-third\nof all of our traffic to our web"},{"time":155920,"text":"clusters to the English Wikipedia,"},{"time":157580,"text":"which is surprising to a lot of people."},{"time":159462,"text":"A lot of people think in a very\nEnglish-centric way on the Internet,"},{"time":162840,"text":"but for us, we're truly global."},{"time":164760,"text":"We're in many, many languages."},{"time":166880,"text":"How popular we've gotten to be --\nwe're a top-50 website"},{"time":170040,"text":"and we're more popular\nthan the New York Times."},{"time":172255,"text":"So this is where we get\nto Yochai's discussion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176960,"text":"This shows the growth of Wikipedia --\nwe're the blue line there --"},{"time":180320,"text":"and this is the New York Times over there."},{"time":183040,"text":"And what's interesting about this"},{"time":184640,"text":"is the New York Times website is a huge,\nenormous corporate operation"},{"time":189000,"text":"with I have no idea\nhow many hundreds of employees."},{"time":191520,"text":"We have exactly one employee,"},{"time":193560,"text":"and that employee\nis our lead software developer."},{"time":196200,"text":"And he's only been our employee\nsince January 2005,"},{"time":199400,"text":"all the other growth before that ..."},{"time":201240,"text":"So the servers are managed\nby a ragtag band of volunteers."},{"time":204880,"text":"All the editing is done by volunteers."},{"time":206880,"text":"And the way that we're organized"},{"time":208440,"text":"is not like any traditional\norganization you can imagine."},{"time":211147,"text":"People are always asking,\n\"Well, who's in charge of this?\""},{"time":213886,"text":"or \"Who does that?\""},{"time":215080,"text":"And the answer is:\nanybody who wants to pitch in."},{"time":217400,"text":"It's a very unusual and chaotic thing."},{"time":221480,"text":"We've got over 90 servers now\nin three locations."},{"time":223800,"text":"These are managed by volunteer\nsystem administrators who are online."},{"time":229080,"text":"I can go online\nany time of the day or night"},{"time":231160,"text":"and see eight to 10 people waiting for me"},{"time":235480,"text":"to ask a question or something,\nanything about the servers."},{"time":239040,"text":"You could never afford\nto do this in a company."},{"time":241400,"text":"You could never afford"},{"time":242640,"text":"to have a standby crew of people\n24 hours a day"},{"time":246400,"text":"and do what we're doing at Wikipedia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":249480,"text":"So we're doing around\n1.4 billion page views monthly,"},{"time":252720,"text":"so it's really gotten to be a huge thing."},{"time":255360,"text":"And everything is managed\nby the volunteers."},{"time":257760,"text":"And the total monthly cost\nfor our bandwidth is about 5,000 dollars."},{"time":262000,"text":"And that's essentially our main cost."},{"time":263960,"text":"We could actually do without the employee."},{"time":266240,"text":"We hired Brian because he was\nworking part-time for two years"},{"time":270680,"text":"and full-time at Wikipedia,"},{"time":272000,"text":"so we actually hired him,"},{"time":273240,"text":"so he could get a life\nand go to the movies sometimes."},{"time":276955,"text":"So the big question when you've got\nthis really chaotic organization is,"},{"time":280360,"text":"why isn't it all rubbish?"},{"time":281600,"text":"Why is the website as good as it is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283995,"text":"First of all, how good is it?"},{"time":285400,"text":"Well, it's pretty good."},{"time":286960,"text":"It isn't perfect,"},{"time":288200,"text":"but it's much better\nthan you would expect,"},{"time":290240,"text":"given our completely chaotic model."},{"time":291947,"text":"So when you saw him make\na ridiculous edit to the page about me,"},{"time":294987,"text":"you think, \"Oh, this is obviously\njust going to degenerate into rubbish.\""},{"time":298760,"text":"But when we've seen quality tests --"},{"time":300515,"text":"and there haven't been enough of these yet"},{"time":302555,"text":"and I'm really encouraging\npeople to do more,"},{"time":305160,"text":"comparing Wikipedia\nto traditional things --"},{"time":307320,"text":"we win hands down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309120,"text":"So a German magazine\ncompared German Wikipedia,"},{"time":311880,"text":"which is much, much smaller than English,"},{"time":315240,"text":"to Microsoft Encarta\nand to Brockhaus multimedial,"},{"time":319360,"text":"and we won across the board."},{"time":320840,"text":"They hired experts to come and look\nat articles and compare the quality,"},{"time":324245,"text":"and we were very pleased with that result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327320,"text":"So a lot of people have heard about\nthe Wikipedia Bush-Kerry controversy."},{"time":332880,"text":"The media has covered this\nsomewhat extensively."},{"time":335560,"text":"It started out\nwith an article in Red Herring."},{"time":338400,"text":"The reporters called me up and they --"},{"time":340240,"text":"I mean, I have to say\nthey spelled my name right,"},{"time":343240,"text":"but they really wanted to say\nthe Bush-Kerry election is so contentious,"},{"time":348200,"text":"it's tearing apart\nthe Wikipedia community."},{"time":350600,"text":"And so they quote me as saying,"},{"time":352120,"text":"\"They're the most contentious\nin the history of Wikipedia.\""},{"time":355040,"text":"What I actually said\nis they're not contentious at all."},{"time":357640,"text":"So it's a slight misquote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361560,"text":"The articles were edited quite heavily."},{"time":363600,"text":"And it is true that we did\nhave to lock the articles"},{"time":366080,"text":"on a couple of occasions."},{"time":367440,"text":"Time magazine recently reported that"},{"time":369840,"text":"\"Extreme action sometimes has to be taken,"},{"time":371880,"text":"and Wales locked the entries\non Kerry and Bush for most of 2004.\""},{"time":376760,"text":"This came after I told the reporter\nthat we had to lock it for --"},{"time":381040,"text":"occasionally a little bit here and there."},{"time":383200,"text":"So the truth in general\nis that the kinds of controversies"},{"time":386600,"text":"that you would probably think\nwe have within the Wikipedia community"},{"time":389815,"text":"are not really controversies at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392560,"text":"Articles on controversial topics\nare edited a lot,"},{"time":395080,"text":"but they don't cause much controversy\nwithin the community."},{"time":398080,"text":"And the reason for this is that most\npeople understand the need for neutrality."},{"time":402600,"text":"The real struggle is not\nbetween the right and the left --"},{"time":409320,"text":"that's where most people assume --"},{"time":410964,"text":"but it's between\nthe party of the thoughtful"},{"time":413040,"text":"and the party of the jerks."},{"time":414360,"text":"And no side of the political spectrum"},{"time":416200,"text":"has a monopoly\non either of those qualities."},{"time":418680,"text":"The actual truth\nabout the specific Bush-Kerry incident"},{"time":421280,"text":"is that the Bush-Kerry articles"},{"time":424280,"text":"were locked less than one percent\nof the time in 2004,"},{"time":427280,"text":"and it wasn't because\nthey were contentious;"},{"time":429360,"text":"it was just because\nthere was routine vandalism --"},{"time":431720,"text":"which happens sometimes even on stage ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436600,"text":"Sometimes even reporters have reported\nto me that they vandalized Wikipedia"},{"time":440160,"text":"and were amazed\nthat it was fixed so quickly."},{"time":442520,"text":"And I said -- you know, I always say,\nplease don't do that."},{"time":445320,"text":"That's not a good thing."},{"time":446920,"text":"So how do we do this?"},{"time":448440,"text":"How do we manage the quality control?"},{"time":451320,"text":"How does it work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":454120,"text":"So there's a few elements,"},{"time":455840,"text":"mostly social policies\nand some elements of the software."},{"time":459120,"text":"So the biggest\nand the most important thing"},{"time":461880,"text":"is our neutral point of view policy."},{"time":463635,"text":"This is something\nthat I set down, from the very beginning,"},{"time":466421,"text":"as a core principle of the community\nthat's completely not debatable."},{"time":470480,"text":"It's a social concept of cooperation,"},{"time":473400,"text":"so we don't talk a lot\nabout truth and objectivity."},{"time":476920,"text":"The reason for this is if we say"},{"time":479000,"text":"we're only going to write\nthe \"truth\" about some topic,"},{"time":481600,"text":"that doesn't do us a damn bit of good\nof figuring out what to write,"},{"time":484831,"text":"because I don't agree with you\nabout what's the truth."},{"time":487391,"text":"But we have this\njargon term of neutrality,"},{"time":489760,"text":"which has its own long history\nwithin the community,"},{"time":492240,"text":"which basically says,\nany time there's a controversial issue,"},{"time":495680,"text":"Wikipedia itself should not\ntake a stand on the issue."},{"time":498280,"text":"We should merely report on what\nreputable parties have said about it."},{"time":501543,"text":"So this neutrality policy\nis really important for us"},{"time":504640,"text":"because it empowers a community\nthat is very diverse"},{"time":507920,"text":"to come together\nand actually get some work done."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510240,"text":"So we have very diverse contributors"},{"time":512400,"text":"in terms of political,\nreligious, cultural backgrounds."},{"time":515640,"text":"By having this firm neutrality policy,"},{"time":517480,"text":"which is non-negotiable\nfrom the beginning,"},{"time":519520,"text":"we ensure that people can work together"},{"time":521402,"text":"and that the entries\ndon't become simply a war"},{"time":523640,"text":"back and forth\nbetween the left and the right."},{"time":525807,"text":"If you engage in that type of behavior,\nyou'll be asked to leave the community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531240,"text":"So, real-time peer review."},{"time":532720,"text":"Every single change on the site\ngoes to the \"Recent changes\" page."},{"time":535880,"text":"So as soon as he made his change,\nit went to the \"Recent changes\" page."},{"time":539400,"text":"That recent changes page\nwas also fed into an IRC channel,"},{"time":543400,"text":"which is an Internet chat channel"},{"time":545000,"text":"that people are monitoring\nwith various software tools."},{"time":548920,"text":"And people can get RSS feeds --"},{"time":551400,"text":"they can get email\nnotifications of changes."},{"time":554520,"text":"And then users can set up\ntheir own personal watch list."},{"time":557200,"text":"So my page is on quite a few\nvolunteers' watch lists,"},{"time":559717,"text":"because it is sometimes vandalized."},{"time":561437,"text":"And therefore, what happens is someone\nwill notice the change very quickly,"},{"time":567440,"text":"and then they'll just\nsimply revert the change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570840,"text":"There's a \"new pages feed,\" for example,"},{"time":572780,"text":"so you can go\nto a certain page of Wikipedia"},{"time":574860,"text":"and see every new page as it's created."},{"time":576820,"text":"This is really important"},{"time":577980,"text":"because a lot of new pages\nare just garbage that has to be deleted,"},{"time":581200,"text":"you know, \"ASDFASDF.\""},{"time":582480,"text":"But also, that's some\nof the most interesting and fun things,"},{"time":585420,"text":"some of the new articles."},{"time":586660,"text":"People will start an article\non some interesting topic,"},{"time":589260,"text":"other people will find that intriguing"},{"time":591100,"text":"and jump in and help\nand make it much better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593520,"text":"So we do have edits by anonymous users,"},{"time":595440,"text":"which is one of the most controversial\nand intriguing things about Wikipedia."},{"time":599320,"text":"So, Chris was able to do his change --\nhe didn't have to log in or anything;"},{"time":602960,"text":"he just went on the website\nand made a change."},{"time":605800,"text":"But it turns out\nthat only about 18 percent"},{"time":607880,"text":"of all the edits to the website"},{"time":609400,"text":"are done by anonymous users."},{"time":610760,"text":"And that's a really important\nthing to understand:"},{"time":613120,"text":"the vast majority of the edits\nthat go on on the website"},{"time":616400,"text":"are from a very close-knit community\nof maybe 600 to 1,000 people"},{"time":620120,"text":"who are in constant communication."},{"time":621764,"text":"And we have over 40 IRC channels,\n40 mailing lists."},{"time":624360,"text":"All these people know each other."},{"time":625960,"text":"They communicate.\nWe have off-line meetings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628032,"text":"These are the people\nwho are doing the bulk of the site,"},{"time":630676,"text":"and they are, in a sense,\nsemi-professionals at what they're doing."},{"time":635960,"text":"The standards we set for ourselves"},{"time":638320,"text":"are equal to or higher\nthan professional standards of quality."},{"time":641400,"text":"We don't always meet those standards,\nbut that's what we're striving for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644940,"text":"And so that tight community\nis who really cares for the site,"},{"time":647822,"text":"and these are some\nof the smartest people I've ever met."},{"time":650480,"text":"It's my job to say that,\nbut it's actually true."},{"time":652760,"text":"The type of people who were drawn\nto writing an encyclopedia for fun"},{"time":656520,"text":"tend to be pretty smart people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658880,"text":"The tools and the software:\nthere's lots of tools that allow us --"},{"time":662000,"text":"allow us, meaning the community --"},{"time":663644,"text":"to self-monitor\nand to monitor all the work."},{"time":665720,"text":"This is an example\nof a page history on \"flat Earth,\""},{"time":668240,"text":"and you can see some changes\nthat were made."},{"time":670320,"text":"What's nice about this page\nis you can immediately take a look at this"},{"time":673640,"text":"and see, \"OK, I understand now.\""},{"time":675240,"text":"When somebody goes and looks at --"},{"time":677040,"text":"they see that someone,\nan anonymous IP number,"},{"time":679207,"text":"made an edit to my page."},{"time":680720,"text":"That sounds suspicious.\nWho is this person?"},{"time":682800,"text":"Somebody looks at it --"},{"time":684040,"text":"they can immediately see\nhighlighted in red"},{"time":686080,"text":"all of the changes that took place --"},{"time":688000,"text":"to see, OK, well, these words\nhave changed, things like this."},{"time":691640,"text":"So that's one tool that we can use"},{"time":693284,"text":"to very quickly monitor\nthe history of a page."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696520,"text":"Another thing that we do\nwithin the community"},{"time":698840,"text":"is we leave everything very open-ended."},{"time":702240,"text":"Most of the social rules\nand the methods of work"},{"time":705640,"text":"are left completely open-ended\nin the software."},{"time":708080,"text":"All of that stuff is just on Wiki pages."},{"time":710120,"text":"And so there's nothing\nin the software that enforces the rules."},{"time":713240,"text":"The example I've got up here\nis the Votes for Deletion page."},{"time":717280,"text":"So, I mentioned earlier,\npeople type \"ASDFASDF\" --"},{"time":719880,"text":"it needs to be deleted."},{"time":721120,"text":"Cases like that,\nthe administrators just delete it."},{"time":723620,"text":"There's no reason\nto have a big argument about it."},{"time":725980,"text":"But you can imagine there's a lot\nof other areas where the question is,"},{"time":729339,"text":"is this notable enough\nto go in an encyclopedia?"},{"time":731603,"text":"Is the information verifiable?\nIs it a hoax? Is it true? Is it what?"},{"time":735200,"text":"So we needed a social method\nfor figuring out the answer to this."},{"time":738280,"text":"And so the method that arose\norganically within the community"},{"time":741162,"text":"is the Votes For Deletion page."},{"time":742760,"text":"And in the particular\nexample we have here,"},{"time":744800,"text":"it's a film, \"Twisted Issues,\""},{"time":746320,"text":"and the first person says,"},{"time":747800,"text":"\"Now this is supposedly a film.\nIt fails the Google test miserably.\""},{"time":751520,"text":"The Google test is you look in Google\nand see if it's there,"},{"time":754360,"text":"because if something's not even in Google,\nit probably doesn't exist at all."},{"time":758280,"text":"It's not a perfect rule,"},{"time":759880,"text":"but it's a nice starting point\nfor quick research."},{"time":763240,"text":"So somebody says, \"Delete it, please.\nDelete it -- it's not notable.\""},{"time":766519,"text":"And then somebody says,\n\"Wait, I found it. I found it in a book,"},{"time":769559,"text":"'Film Threat Video Guide:\nthe 20 Underground Films You Must See.'\""},{"time":772840,"text":"So the next persons says, \"Clean it up.\""},{"time":774769,"text":"Somebody says, \"I've found it on IMDB.\nKeep, keep, keep.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":778200,"text":"And what's interesting about this\nis that the software is --"},{"time":781040,"text":"these votes are just text\ntyped into a page."},{"time":784600,"text":"This is not really a vote\nso much as it is a dialogue."},{"time":788680,"text":"Now it is true that at the end of the day,"},{"time":791440,"text":"an administrator can go through here\nand take a look at this and say,"},{"time":794703,"text":"\"OK, 18 deletes, two keeps:\nwe'll delete it.\""},{"time":797200,"text":"But in other cases,\nthis could be 18 deletes and two keeps,"},{"time":801000,"text":"and we would keep it,\nbecause if those last two keeps say,"},{"time":803820,"text":"\"Wait a minute. Nobody else saw this\nbut I found it in a book,"},{"time":806749,"text":"and I found a link\nto a page that describes it,"},{"time":808971,"text":"and I'm going to clean it up tomorrow,\nso please don't delete it,\""},{"time":812091,"text":"then it would survive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813300,"text":"And it also matters\nwho the people are who are voting."},{"time":815920,"text":"Like I say, it's a tight-knit community."},{"time":817849,"text":"Down here at the bottom,\n\"Keep, real movie,\" RickK."},{"time":820400,"text":"RickK is a very famous Wikipedian\nwho does an enormous amount of work"},{"time":823805,"text":"with vandalism, hoaxes\nand votes for deletion."},{"time":826560,"text":"His voice carries a lot of weight\nwithin the community"},{"time":829400,"text":"because he knows what he's doing."},{"time":832400,"text":"So how is all this governed?"},{"time":834360,"text":"People really want to know\nabout administrators, things like that."},{"time":837520,"text":"So the Wikipedia governance model,\nthe governance of the community,"},{"time":841400,"text":"is a very confusing,\nbut workable mix of consensus --"},{"time":845840,"text":"meaning we try not to vote\non the content of articles,"},{"time":848400,"text":"because the majority view\nis not necessarily neutral --"},{"time":852320,"text":"some amount of democracy --"},{"time":853640,"text":"all of the administrators --"},{"time":855000,"text":"these are the people\nwho have the ability to delete pages."},{"time":857820,"text":"That doesn't mean that they have\nthe right to delete pages."},{"time":860680,"text":"They still have to follow all the rules --\nbut they're elected by the community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864540,"text":"Sometimes people --\nrandom trolls on the Internet --"},{"time":866994,"text":"like to accuse me\nof handpicking the administrators"},{"time":869401,"text":"to bias the content of the encyclopedia."},{"time":871330,"text":"I always laugh at this, because I have\nno idea how they're elected, actually."},{"time":875120,"text":"There's a certain amount of aristocracy."},{"time":877120,"text":"You got a hint of that\nwhen I mentioned, like,"},{"time":879287,"text":"RickK's voice would carry\na lot more weight"},{"time":881463,"text":"than someone we don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882783,"text":"I give this talk sometimes with Angela,"},{"time":885520,"text":"who was just re-elected to the board\nfrom the community --"},{"time":888275,"text":"to the Board of the Foundation,"},{"time":889795,"text":"with more than twice the votes\nof the person who didn't make it."},{"time":892960,"text":"And I always embarrass her because I say,"},{"time":895920,"text":"\"Well, Angela, for example,"},{"time":897240,"text":"could get away with doing\nabsolutely anything within Wikipedia,"},{"time":900680,"text":"because she's so admired and so powerful.\""},{"time":902720,"text":"But the irony is, of course, that Angela\ncan do this because she's the one person"},{"time":906560,"text":"who you know would never, ever\nbreak any rules of Wikipedia."},{"time":909560,"text":"And I also like to say\nshe's the only person"},{"time":911640,"text":"who actually knows\nall the rules of Wikipedia, so ..."},{"time":914880,"text":"And then there's monarchy,"},{"time":916143,"text":"and that's my role\non the community, so ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918183,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920600,"text":"I was describing this in Berlin once,"},{"time":923240,"text":"and the next day\nin the newspaper the headline said,"},{"time":926040,"text":"\"I am the Queen of England.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":927632,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":928807,"text":"And that's not exactly what I said, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":932720,"text":"the point is my role in the community --"},{"time":935320,"text":"Within the free software world,\nthere's been a long-standing tradition"},{"time":940040,"text":"of the \"benevolent dictator\" model."},{"time":943280,"text":"So if you look at most\nof the major free software projects,"},{"time":946160,"text":"they have one single person in charge"},{"time":947960,"text":"who everyone agrees\nis the benevolent dictator."},{"time":951320,"text":"Well, I don't like the term\n\"benevolent dictator,\""},{"time":953840,"text":"and I don't think that it's my job\nor my role in the world of ideas"},{"time":957840,"text":"to be the dictator of the future\nof all human knowledge"},{"time":961200,"text":"compiled by the world."},{"time":962440,"text":"It just isn't appropriate."},{"time":964160,"text":"But there is a need still\nfor a certain amount of monarchy,"},{"time":966960,"text":"a certain amount of --"},{"time":968560,"text":"sometimes we have to make a decision"},{"time":970360,"text":"and we don't want\nto get bogged down too heavily"},{"time":972623,"text":"in formal decision-making processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975360,"text":"So as an example\nof how this can be important:"},{"time":980280,"text":"we recently had a situation where\na neo-Nazi website discovered Wikipedia,"},{"time":984280,"text":"and they said,\n\"Oh, well, this is horrible,"},{"time":987160,"text":"this Jewish conspiracy of a website,"},{"time":989080,"text":"and we're going to get certain articles\ndeleted that we don't like."},{"time":992263,"text":"And we see they have a voting process,\nso we're going to send --"},{"time":995287,"text":"we have 40,000 members\nand we're going to send them over"},{"time":998120,"text":"and they're all going to vote\nand get these pages deleted.\""},{"time":1000922,"text":"Well, they managed\nto get 18 people to show up."},{"time":1003137,"text":"That's neo-Nazi math for you."},{"time":1005920,"text":"They always think they've got\n40,000 members when they've got 18."},{"time":1009400,"text":"But they managed to get 18 people\nto come and vote in a fairly absurd way"},{"time":1012920,"text":"to delete a perfectly valid article."},{"time":1014960,"text":"Of course, the vote ended up\nbeing about 85 to 18,"},{"time":1017720,"text":"so there was no real danger\nto our democratic processes."},{"time":1021000,"text":"On the other hand, people said,\n\"But what are we going to do?"},{"time":1024319,"text":"I mean, this could happen."},{"time":1025599,"text":"What if some group\ngets really seriously organized"},{"time":1027960,"text":"and comes in and wants to vote?\""},{"time":1030560,"text":"Then I said, \"Well, fuck it,\nwe'll just change the rules.\""},{"time":1033359,"text":"That's my job in the community:"},{"time":1035079,"text":"to say we won't allow\nour openness and freedom"},{"time":1038680,"text":"to undermine the quality of the content."},{"time":1041280,"text":"And so, as long as people\ntrust me in my role,"},{"time":1044599,"text":"then that's a valid place for me."},{"time":1046480,"text":"Of course, because of the free licensing,"},{"time":1048540,"text":"if I do a bad job, the volunteers\nare more than happy to take and leave --"},{"time":1052041,"text":"I can't tell anyone what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"So the final point here\nis that to understand how Wikipedia works,"},{"time":1058720,"text":"it's important to understand\nthat our wiki model is the way we work,"},{"time":1061935,"text":"but we are not fanatical web anarchists."},{"time":1065560,"text":"In fact, we're very flexible\nabout the social methodology,"},{"time":1068960,"text":"because ultimately,\nthe passion of the community"},{"time":1071400,"text":"is for the quality of the work,"},{"time":1073440,"text":"not necessarily for the process\nthat we use to generate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076440,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081960,"text":"Ben Saunders: Yeah, hi, Ben Saunders."},{"time":1083760,"text":"Jimmy, you mentioned impartiality\nbeing a key to Wikipedia's success."},{"time":1087920,"text":"It strikes me that much of the textbooks\nthat are used to educate our children"},{"time":1093280,"text":"are inherently biased."},{"time":1095080,"text":"Have you found Wikipedia\nbeing used by teachers"},{"time":1098720,"text":"and how do you see Wikipedia\nchanging education?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101200,"text":"Jimmy Wales: Yeah, so, a lot of teachers\nare beginning to use Wikipedia."},{"time":1105440,"text":"There's a media storyline about Wikipedia,\nwhich I think is false."},{"time":1110040,"text":"It builds on the storyline\nof bloggers versus newspapers."},{"time":1113640,"text":"And the storyline is,\nthere's this crazy thing, Wikipedia,"},{"time":1116800,"text":"but academics hate it\nand teachers hate it."},{"time":1120280,"text":"And that turns out to not be true."},{"time":1122880,"text":"The last time I got an email\nfrom a journalist saying,"},{"time":1125440,"text":"\"Why do academics hate Wikipedia?\""},{"time":1127180,"text":"I sent it from my Harvard email address"},{"time":1129062,"text":"because I was recently\nappointed a fellow there."},{"time":1131339,"text":"And I said, \"Well,\nthey don't all hate it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133379,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134480,"text":"But I think there's going\nto be huge impacts."},{"time":1137360,"text":"And we actually have a project\nthat I'm personally really excited about,"},{"time":1140800,"text":"which is the Wikibooks project,"},{"time":1142320,"text":"which is an effort to create\ntextbooks in all the languages."},{"time":1145440,"text":"And that's a much bigger project."},{"time":1147040,"text":"It's going to take 20 years or so\nto come to fruition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1151680,"text":"But part of that is to fulfill our mission"},{"time":1153720,"text":"of giving an encyclopedia\nto every single person on the planet."},{"time":1156720,"text":"We don't mean we're going\nto Spam them with AOL-style CDs."},{"time":1159600,"text":"We mean we're going to give them\na tool that they can use."},{"time":1162420,"text":"And for a lot of people in the world,"},{"time":1164220,"text":"if I give you an encyclopedia\nthat's written at a university level,"},{"time":1167420,"text":"it doesn't do you any good\nwithout a whole host of literacy materials"},{"time":1171000,"text":"to build you up to the point\nwhere you can actually use it."},{"time":1173800,"text":"The Wikibooks project\nis an effort to do that."},{"time":1175967,"text":"And I think that we're going to see --\nit may not even come from us;"},{"time":1179200,"text":"there's all kinds of innovation going on."},{"time":1181200,"text":"But freely licensed textbooks\nare the next big thing in education."}]}]}